Use the standard library
This is how to fib of n:
   When n is 0, then:
      The answer is 0
   End when
   When n is 1, then:
      The answer is 1
   End when
   The answer is sum of (fib of (diff of n and 1)) and (fib of (diff of n and 2))
Now you know

>>> fib of 10
55
>>> fib of 1
1
>>> fib of 8
21